name: Social Entrepreneurs
about:
Our mission is to improve the lives of people by helping organizations realize their potential.

We serve nonprofit community service providers, state and local government agencies, state associations and foundations throughout the United States.

We offer a full range of top quality professional services to assist nonprofit and public organizations with virtually any type of planning, organizational development, evaluation or operational situation. 

We provide expert guidance for all types of planning needs, from planning new programs within a single agency to planning for statewide systems of services. Our planning services include long-range strategic planning, assessment of community assets and needs, operational (business) planning, shorter-range implementation planning, program/service planning, and fund distribution planning for public agencies and foundation. 

Sustainability. For health and human services, sustainability is the ability to create lasting improvements in health and well-being for an extended period of time despite ongoing changes in funding sources, program models, community demographics and other factors. Our sustainability services use a uniquely holistic approach to address all of the factors shown by research to lead to long-term stability and success in maintaining important community outcomes.


Governance. We can enhance the effectiveness of governing bodies in many ways, including assessment of current functioning, training, team building and optimized board design, bylaws and other operating guidelines.

Facilitation. Our consultants are trained in numerous facilitation methods and can prepare and facilitate engaging and highly productive meetings, retreats, focus groups, community forums and other events with any type and size of group.

Capacity building. Strengthening the internal capacity of organizations is a cornerstone of our work.

name: Extraordinary Families
about:
in 2014 Southern California Foster Family & Adoption Agency merged with Child Welfare Initiative to form Extraordinary Families. Please see our website to learn more about our expanded mission and services www.extraordinaryfamilies.org. 

Follow ExtraordinaryFamilies on Facebook https://www.facebook.com/ExtraordinaryFamilies/?ref=aymt_homepage_panel and Linked In https://www.linkedin.com/company/extraordinaryfamilies?trk=biz-companies-cym


Southern California Foster Family and Adoption Agency, a private, non-profit corporation, was started in 1994, dedicated to helping abused, abandoned and neglected children find secure, stable and nurturing homes.  The agency provides for the well being of children in its care and helps them become independent and successful adults.

Southern California Foster Family and Adoption Agency (SCFFAA) serves the greater Los Angeles community by providing quality homes for children of all ages, from newborn to 21 years old.  The agency provides for sibling groups, children with developmental delays, behavioral and school problems.

The agency seeks and supports loving, caring and capable families who want to bring a child or children into their home.  Whether interested in foster or adoptive parenting, all prospective families must be able to provide, with financial assistance from the agency, a secure, stable and nurturing home for the children.

All capable families are welcome regardless of age, sex, race, ethnicity, religion, sexual orientation, gender identity, physical characteristics, marital or domestic partnership status, medical or disability status.

SCFFAA complies with Title XXII regulations as impletmented by the State Department of Social Services, Community Care Licensing Division, and the Los Angeles County Department of Children and Family Services contract provisions.

Los Angeles, CA 90026

name: AMVETS Hawaii
about:
AMERICAN VETERANS HAWAII [AMVETS Hawaii]

AMVETS Hawaii Service Foundation Corp (https://amvets-hawaii.org), is headed by Commander Donovan A. Lazarus, President & CEO.  AMVETS Hawaii Service Foundation is a 501c3, public non profit organization established to help raise the needed funds for AMVETS Department of Hawaii‚Äôs programs in the areas of human services, veterans, and youth. Funding is intended to provide veterans and the community with basic needs such as housing and nutrition, and to support youth programs aimed at helping youth become contributing members of society.

AMVETS Department of Hawaii (https://amvetshawaii.org), is headed by AMVETS Department of Hawaii, State Commander Donovan A. Lazarus.  AMVETS Department of Hawaii is a nonprofit 501c19, military membership organization for members of the United States Armed Forces (current and past), established under American Veterans (AMVETS) National (https://amvets.org), a Congressionally-chartered, nonprofit 501c19, Veterans Service Organization (VSO).

Mission:
AMVETS Hawaii mission is to provide service, support and assistance for all who served honorably in the United States Armed Forces: past, present and future veterans and their families.

The AMVETS West Oahu Veterans Center is located at 5001 Iroquois Avenue, Building 612 & 612A, West Lock Annex, Ewa Beach, Hawaii 96706. The 3030-square-foot facility will accommodate military and community organizations, a gathering place for meetings, workshops, recreation activities and other events for the betterment of our veterans. Wireless Internet service is available throughout the facility.  

The facility and on-site staff are fully connected to AMVETS National Headquarters (https://amvets.org). The on-site communication, liaison, and coordination functions enable our clients to utilize all AMVETS National resources and services.

Hours of operation: 0800-2400 daily (7-days).  After hours for special events requires Navy Facility (NAVFAC) Hawaii, JBPHH.

name: EFELA - European Federation Of Energy Law Associations
about:
Energy is an essential component of social and economic life. For more than sixty years energy has been at the core of the European project and it keeps a crucial role concerning cohesion, jobs, investments and innovation in Europe. 
Over the last two decades, energy has deserved increased attention of the legislator for its social, political and economic significance and for its interrelation with other economic and industrial sectors and public policies, in particular climate change. At the same time, there has been an extraordinary transformation of the energy sector, driven by three phenomena of a different but concurrent nature:

- on the one hand, growing technological innovation;
- on the other hand, the need to ensure that energy transformation and use is compatible with environmental goals and the fight against climate change and, 
- finally, the convergence of the energy sector with other sectors such as transport, buildings, telecommunications, water and waste management, as well as information and communication technologies.

The Energy Transition requires a complex framework of legal relations involving many agents across the European Union. Therefore, Energy Law became one of the central chapters of the new public law of economic nature with its own principles, problems, methods and regulatory techniques.

For all the above, a group of energy law experts from different countries of the European Union, through the national associations specialized in this matter, have decided to constitute the European Federation of Energy Law Associations. Our goal is to promote reflection, study, research and discussion of all issues related to the configuration of a modern Energy Law, thus contributing to the making of more efficient energy markets, enhancing coherence of the reliant legal and regulatory frameworks throughout Europe.

name: Elenor Fabrics
about:
With its factory located in Bursa, it exports its fabrics to more than 41 countries of the world and serves to more than 1.000 retailers and interior architects around the world with its Stocked Cutting and Contract collection. 
Elenor Textile started its production activities in 2008 and operates in the fields of home, hotel and hospital textiles.  Elenor Tekstil, which is the main production subject of Curtain and Decorative fabrics, has added qualities such as flame retardancy, anti-bacteriality and stain resistancy  to its products with its technical textile investments.
Our fabrics, which are inspired by nature, create a soft, minimalist and modern atmosphere in the houses by pairing with each other easily. With the new fabrics we add regularly, we have a collection that always updates itself and follows the fashion.

name: Enactus CVS
about:
Enactus is the world‚Äôs largest experiential learning platform dedicated to creating a better world while developing the next generation of entrepreneurial leaders and social innovators.
The Enactus network of global business, academic and student leaders are unified by a vision to create a better, sustainable world.

We at Enactus CVS aim to act as the epitome of change. A team of 70+ dynamic individuals united towards a common goal of rising by lifting others.


Our current projects include:

Project Abyaan: Project Abyaan aims to convert Used Cooking Oil(UCO) into soaps while uplifting underprivileged women and promoting hygiene and sanitation. Our project has two verticals namely Ayuda: A soap made out of UCO and Ayuda Skincare Plus range that features 2 types of soaps, made out of goat milk and used coffee ground.


Project Ehtiyaat: A collaborative project that aims to upcycle single-use plastic waste and transform it into plarn, while reviving the disappearing art of traditional craftsmanship while supporting the artists. Ehtiyaat aims not only to attenuate the issue of Single-use plastic waste but also to empower the traditional handloom communities by providing them with financial independence.
Ehtiyaat offers a variety of customisable products like laptop sleeves, handbags, coin pouches, Plas-kits and Plarnters.

name: Fapas
about:
Established in 1990, Fapas is a world recognised provider of proficiency tests, running over 600 tests annually across an extensive range of matrices and analytes for the food and water, environmental chemistry and microbiology sectors. Taking part in our proficiency tests provides you with the confidence in your laboratory equipment, methods and staff, and assurance that you are delivering the quality results required by your customers.

We provide our participants with a confidential service that allows you to participate at a level that suits you; there is no minimum number of proficiency tests that you must take part in each year. Proficiency testing is an essential part of laboratory quality procedure and participation is a mandatory requirement of ISO 17025 accreditation. 

Fapas covers chemical analysis of real food samples for a wide range of target analytes including: nutritional components, additives, natural contaminants, pesticide and veterinary medicine residues, and packaging chemical migrants. Comprehensive reports provide information on analytical methods used by other participants as well as historic trend analysis and follows international guidelines for proficiency testing and is accredited by UKAS to ISO/IEC 17043.  With our Food Microbiology programme we offer 10 distributions throughout the year giving you the flexibility to choose what you need and when where as our GM programme covers the detection and/or enumeration of genetically modified material in food samples, including soya and maize.

Our Water & Environmental scheme assesses the performance of laboratories in water and environmental testing sectors. The scheme satisfies the UK Drinking Water Inspectorate (DWI) requirements for the Water Supply (Water Quality) Regulation 2010: Regulation 16, Appendix 1 for both chemical and microbiological parameters.

about:
We live in an ever changing world with never ending breaking news. The information technology is in a competition to bring you the news updates. Though there are alternative media which provides open platform for discussion and report, most of the medias neglect the indigenous and marginalized communities. But E-Vartha outstands always to support the oppressed and the marginalized people and keeps a progressive approach towards the contemporary issues of the world.

E-Vartha is one of the leading Multilingual(Malayalam & English) news portals since 2009 (www.evartha.in). Its operations are being controlled and updated from Trivandrum by highly talented youngsters with good technical background.

Millions use online portals as a media for information thus, evartha has achieved the task of reaching these millions of malayalees who are around the world. Moreover, evartha is also used as a platform for the leading business ads which are part of everyday life.



Following are the key features of E-Vartha;

E-Vartha is aggradated by the government of Kerala with I & PRD aggradations (21674/D3/12/I&PR) and listed among the Government media list.
E- Vartha is a member of Digital News Media Federation(kerala) (DNMF)
E- Vartha is counted among the top ten positions in the Google news list
E- Vartha has a reputable position in national and Global Alexa Ranking.
E- Vartha has readers from more than 120 countries, mostly from India, Middle East, UK, US.
E-Vartha covers wider areas of news including national, international, business, sports and entertainment with an aim to reach all age groups with current world affairs.
E- Vartha is currently aiming to launch its editions in Middle East, UK and US regions.

name: RoadHog
about:
RoadHog, Inc. offers a complete line of self-contained asphalt milling equipment.  The RoadHog series features units with their own engine, hydraulics and electrical system, eliminating any need for auxiliary power requirements from the host vehicle.  RoadHogs are available in 18" to 96" wide cutting widths, equipped with 67, 148, 225 and 275hp Caterpillar Tier 4 Final engines which can be used on a variety of host vehicles including Wheel Loaders, Skidsteers and Compact Track Loaders.

The RoadHog is ideal for milling asphalt or concrete prior to overlay, repairing potholes, road and shoulder reclamation, full depth reclamation (FDR), mechanical and chemical soil stabilization and cutting utility trenches, as the milled material is recycled in place and can be used for base reconstruction or trench backfill.

In addition to these RoadHog series of milling attachments, RoadHog, Inc. manufactures a complete line of hydraulically powered cold planers and road saws for use on any & all makes & models of mini excavators, skidsteer loaders and compact track loaders.

For more information, please visit to our website: www.roadhoginc.com

name: EUROCARE
about:
Eurocare is an alliance of non-governmental public health and social organisations working on the prevention and reduction of alcohol related harm in Europe. Eurocare was formed in 1990 by 9 organisations concerned with the impact of the European Union on Alcohol Policy in Member States. It now has more than 50 member organisations across Europe, most of which are national or supranational umbrella organisations. The organisation has a Secretariat in Brussels, which acts as the central contact point for member organisations as well as other bodies concerned with alcohol related issues, including national and international press.

Eurocare and all members are not affiliated and does not receive any funding from the alcohol industry or any of its social aspect organisations.

The overall goal for Eurocare is to:
- Raise awareness among European, national and regional decision makers of the harms caused by alcohol (social, health and economic burden) ensuring that these are taken into consideration in all relevant EU policy discussions
- Promote the development and implementation of evidence-based policies aimed at effectively preventing and reducing this burden

name: Cool City Avionics
about:
Spectrum Innovates Pathway Program is a 12 month transition experience, for young adults on the autism spectrum as they navigate the
path to college, employment and adult life who share an interest in
aeronautics, aviation, engineering or technology.

In this experiential learning environment, projects with real world applications are conceived and worked on in a combination of collaborative and individual efforts, where students learn the skills of collaboration. team building, planning, implementation, etiquette and safety while developing and absorbing crucial social / emotional and life skills.

Students successfully completing the program receive a certificate, 13
college credits and fast track admission to Vaughn College and the
myriad career programs they offer. Vaughn provides career program graduates with extensive career placement assistance. Alternatively, students may apply to other institutions or pursue entry positions in the workforce.

Development of SIPP is funded in part by an Advanced Technological
Education grant from the National Science Foundation.

about:
EuroCarbo Benelux B.V. is opgericht in 1995. Ons eerste doel was destijds om de levering van industri√´le en voedingsmiddelengassen in MicroBulk  mogelijk te maken voor onze bestaande klanten. Vervolgens zijn wij ons gaan richten op de vervanging van gascilinders en cilinderpakketten door MicroBulk bij alle gebruikers van industri√´le en voedingsmiddelengassen in de Benelux

Meer dan 100 jaar ervaring

EuroCarbo maakt onderdeel uit van ZNKC GAS Groep B.V, een Europese speler met meer dan 100 jaar ervaring 
in industri√´le en voedingsgassen. ZNKC GAS Groep is op haar beurt voortgekomen uit Stoombierbrouwerij Juliana, waar naast bier ook koolstofdioxide werd geproduceerd. Al sinds 1895 levert ZNKC GAS Groep koolstofdioxide in cilinders en later ook in bulk. Hiermee is onze firma de oudste, nog actieve gassenleverancier in de Benelux.  

Dankzij onze innovatiekracht  en ambitieuze instelling, het centraal stellen van de klant en de betrokkenheid van onze medewerkers, is ons familiebedrijf uitgegroeid tot de marktleider in het leveren van MicroBulk in de Benelux. EuroCarbo levert gassen binnen een straal van 300 kilometer rondom onze productielocatie te Sittard.
 
Als √©√©n van de eerste Europese  gassenleveranciers, hebben wij in 1994 de levering van MicroBulk ge√Øntroduceerd en in Europa aan de basis gestaan van deze innovatieve ontwikkeling. Wij onderscheiden ons binnen de gassenindustrie door een duidelijke focus op de levering van MicroBulk-gassen en een gedegen advisering over het gebruik ervan. 

Zodra het gasverbruik van een van onze afnemers de overstap van cilinderpakketten naar een MicroBulk tank rechtvaardigt, dan wordt dit door ons pro-actief geadviseerd. Ook dragen wij er zorg voor dat de ter beschikking 
gestelde cilinderpakketten uit de roulatie worden gehaald, zodat de klant hier verder geen omkijken naar heeft.
 
EuroCarbo - Leading through quality and service, operating more MicroBulk systems than anyone else!

name: Extrusion Alternatives
about:
Why Choose EXALT?
As our name implies, Extrusion Alternatives offers many material options to suit a wide array of tubing applications. We work closely with the leading PVC resin manufacturers like Alpha Cary, Colorite, and Teknor Apex to provide custom medical tubing made from innovative plasticizer formulations and the very latest medical compounds. In addition to these DEHP-Free and Phthalate-Free selections, we offer many alternatives to PVC including: Polyurethane, Thermoplastic Elastomers, and various multi-layer PVC-free formulations.

These flexible products are complemented by a full offering of rigid medical thermoplastics like LDPE, HDPE, Polypropylene, and Nylon. All of these materials are virgin, non-regrind resins, from commercially available sources you know and trust. Our open market approach provides device manufacturers with the largest selection of materials to design to, a clear path to regulatory compliance, and a non-proprietary basis to build devices from.

While design options and material flexibility is our philosophy, it is our uncompromising, single-minded approach to quality that sets us apart. A QR-compliant system not only ensures the tightest in tolerance control, it also dictates that every inch of tubing is run through a pyrogen-controlled process, straight into the confines of a hepa-filtered clean environment for cutting, coiling, inspection, and packaging. From our facility to yours, the end result is better tubing, yielding better devices.

Our open-source material alternative, dedication to high quality products, and customer-centric commitment to service have built our loyal customer following. We welcome the opportunity to earn your business and stand ready to serve your needs.

name: Envirotherm Engineering
about:
Envirotherm is an airconditioning, ventilaiton, refrigeration and solar company based in Johannesburg.
Envirotherm designs, supplies and installs equipment in the residential, commerical, industrial and mining sectors.
Envirotherm supplies various makes of airconditioning units including Daikin, Samsung, Panasonic, LG, Carrier and Toshiba.
Envirotherm supplies and installs different types of airconditioning units including wall mounted splits, under-ceiling splits, ceiling mounted cassettes, ducted hideaways and rooftop package units.

name: East Pennsboro Area School District
about:
East Pennsboro Area School District is a growing, progressive school district with a total population of approximately 2,700 students in kindergarten through grade twelve. Located in Cumberland County, Pennsylvania and bordering on the Susquehanna River, the twelve-square-mile school district serves East Pennsboro Township and the communities of Enola, Summerdale, West Fairview, and parts of Camp Hill.

East Pennsboro is a suburb of the state capital, Harrisburg, and serves a socio-economically diverse community of more than 20,000 citizens. Although it was once considered a railroad town, the community is now thriving as a center for business and service industries. Corporations including EDS, IBM, Gannett-Fleming, Highmark/Blue Shield, and Metro Bank have regional offices within the township.Holy Spirit Health Care System operates a hospital in East Pennsboro and is joined by numerous doctor, dentist, and medical offices.

Bordering the school district campus is a well-regarded post-secondary school ‚Äì Central Pennsylvania College. Within a 40-mile radius of the school district, there are numerous post-secondary schools including Harrisburg Area Community College, Penn State Harrisburg, Messiah College, Dickinson School of Law, Shippensburg University,Lebanon Valley College, Elizabeth town College, and York College of Pennsylvania. Capital Area Intermediate Unit, which provides special education and support services for the region‚Äôs 24 school districts, is also located within East Pennsboro Township. The region offers easy access to a variety of private childcare, nursery, and pre-school facilities.

A strong partnership between the school district and the township has created a supportive atmosphere for a dynamic community.

name: EASD
about:
The European Association for the Study of Diabetes e.V. (EASD) is a membership-based academic non-profit organization. It was founded in 1965 and its headquarters is based in Duesseldorf, Germany.

EASD is a networks for diabetologists with active members from all over the world. Membership is open to scientists, physicians, students, postdocs and fellows, allied health professionals and nurses who are interested in the field of diabetes or related diseases.

The EASD Annual Meeting is one of the largest diabetes conferences in the world, attracting thousands of delegates each year. The scientific programme includes hundreds of talks, presentations and discussions on the latest results from basic and clinical diabetes research.

EASD is also a leading player in postgraduate education having trained thousands of healthcare professionals through dedicated training courses and online education activities. 

The Association is actively involved in producing and endorsing statements and guidelines translating the latest results from diabetes research into best practices in diabetes management. 

By creating the Early Career Academy, EASD has increased its commitment to support, train, mentor, and create opportunities for scientists, clinicians, and students who are at an early or intermediate stage of their career.

The European Foundation for the Study of Diabetes (EFSD) was founded by EASD in 2000 to stimulate diabetes research in Europe. EFSD offers support in all areas of diabetes research through a wide range of joint and stand-alone initiatives. Funding streams are available throughout the year and since inception, EFSD has committed over ‚Ç¨120 million to diabetes research in Europe.

EASD is also the publisher of Diabetologia, a major monthly international diabetes journal with an impact factor of 8.2 (2022). The journal publishes original clinical, translational and experimental research on all aspects of diabetes and related subjects.

name: Professional Editors Guild
about:
Launched in Johannesburg in 1993, PEG is a national body with three branches, Gauteng, Western Cape and KwaZulu-Natal, each run by a committee of volunteers. PEG represents practitioners who operate in the South African publishing industry, corporate communications and media. PEG is a founding member of LAMP (an umbrella Alliance of Language and Media Professionals), whose mission is to promote the interests of all those professionals who serve this key sector of the South African economy. LAMP also represents our sector on book- and reading-development bodies.

PEG‚Äôs members include both freelancers and full-timers who work professionally in any of South Africa‚Äôs nine official languages, plus others: writers, copy-editors, subeditors, overwriters, translators, proofreaders, indexers, book designers, and book and magazine DTP specialists. We also welcome those who are not yet practising but have an interest in the field or wish to make a career in it. We encourage our members to contribute towards the achievement of PEG's objectives. By sharing their professional experience and expertise with colleagues, our members contribute to:
*  elevating and upholding standards of work in the profession
*  improving the public perception of copy-editing and proofreading as a craft
   raising awareness of a much-needed service.

PEG‚Äôs stated objectives are: 
to promote high standards of copy-editing and proofreading
to uphold the professional status of copy-editors and promote professional behaviour among our members
to promote contact among members, the exchange of ideas and the dissemination of information on matters of professional interest
to promote an understanding of the work of copy-editors among potential clients and the general public
to establish and maintain liaison with other societies of copy-editors worldwide.

name: Ethiopiaid
about:
Ethiopiaid Australia is a not-for-profit organisation in Australia raising money for some of the poorest and most vulnerable people in Ethiopia. 

Why Ethiopia?
Despite recent economic growth, Ethiopia is still one of the least developed countries in the world. More than one quarter of the population lives below the national poverty line, only 39% of people can read and write, and 1 in 8 children have lost one or both parents. 

Vision
Our vision is for an Ethiopia free from poverty in which every person has access to quality education, healthcare and a life of dignity.

Mission
Our mission is to break the cycle of poverty in Ethiopia by enabling local communities to realise their potential. We want to contribute to Ethiopia achieving its target of becoming a middle-income country on longer reliant on foreign aid. 

How do we do this?
Our founding principle is that Ethiopians have the answers to the challenges they face. We partner with and provide funding to trusted, local Ethiopian organisations who are specialists in their field. This means we are able to drive change from a grassroots level and alleviate poverty in a way that is realistic, achievable and sustainable.

name: EuMederis Pharmaceuticals
about:
EuMederis Pharmaceuticals carries out design and development of Best in Class peptide pharmaceuticals with improved bioavailability and prolonged duration of action thru the use of our proprietary EuPort modification. 

Our proprietary, non-peptide modification (EuPort) allows rapid identification of best in class clinical candidates. The EuPort platform modification was designed specifically to improve the bioavailability and duration of action of peptide pharmaceuticals. EuPort-modified peptides thus are proprietary new chemical entities with improved and marketable pharmaceutical properties.  

Proof of concept was carried out in osteoporosis, where a fragment of the native parathyroid hormone (PTH1-34; Forteo, Lilly) was further truncated and coupled to the EuPort modification. The resulting molecules have low nanomolar potency and super-agonistic efficacy (cAMP) in human cellular assays, Very prolonged efficacy with no hypercalcemia was demonstrated in vivo. Eu-232 was selected as a clinical candidate.

Modification of an endogenous opioid peptide with the EuPort technology yielded Eu-178, with low nM potency on the mu opioid (morphine-like) receptor and sub-nM antagonistic potency on the delta opioid receptor, a profile for peripheral analgesia with no central side effects (no respiratory depression, euphoria, or addiction).

EuMederis is seeking investors and commercialization partners to bring our preclinical candidates in osteoporosis, pain and asthma into clinical trials.

See the website.

Excellence is hard-earned when it comes to EU-funded programmes.  We all struggle to put promising programmes and bright project ideas to practice, let alone implement them within the stricter parameters set by the EU Regulations for their management and control.  We all know how frustrating it gets when brilliant projects which make a real difference in persons‚Äô lives suffer financial corrections because of administrative shortcomings. What is a Chamber Music Society? We have a trio of core musicians who will perform in most concerts but we also plan to regularly include our amazing colleagues in our performances.

The Fair Trade Chamber Music Society is still evolving, so please watch our website for updates and to see us grow!

Mission Statement: The mission of the Fair Trade Chamber Music Society is to secure a place for classical music in today‚Äôs society by fairly compensating musicians for their artistic endeavors and by seeking new ways to connect with and inspire our audiences. name: EngineeringSpot
about:
The Blog all about Software and Hardware for Design, Engineering and Rapid Prototyping.

EngineeringSpot is a German blog that revolves around all aspects of the digital product development. The portfolio of software tools featured in the blog ranges from the generation, simulation, and visualization
of 3D models to the management of product data to manufacturing.

Additional focus is on the fascinating topic of 3D printing and 3D scanning in the whole range from open
source devices to high-end rapid manufacturing and automated measuring machines.

Coverage of industry events plus exclusive software and hardware tests comprise the wide range of articles on EngineeringSpot.

Ralf Steck is the founder and main author of the EngineeringSpot blog. He studied mechanical engineering
and works as a freelancer journalist. He has more than 20 years of experience in CAD, CAM, PLM, mechanical engineering applications, 3D printing, and computer technology.

The target audience of Engineering-Spot are designers, engineers, and all other participants of the product development process. Germany is a world leader in engineering which makes the readers of the EngineeringSpot blog a really valuable audience.

Blog posts expressing insight and competence, recent news and easy-to-read background texts highlighting new technologies keep readers coming back regularly. Facebook page, Twitter account, and e-mail subscription indicate the availability of new posts to the readership. Typically, two new articles are
posted per week.

Proudly manufacturing in the UK and internationally, our skilled team employs the latest technology for efficient processes, resulting in high-quality products and short lead times.

name: EvangelismCoach.org
about:
I was once the in-your-face obnoxious evangelist, but I've grown in skill and grace. I would talk with everyone whether they wanted to hear me or not, but I now have more fruitful evangelistic conversations that help seekers move closer to Christ.  I've lost the fear that stops me from talking about my faith.

You too can overcome those fears.  

As an evangelist, I want to help seekers and believers connect with a local church so they may grow in grace. Yet many churches are not welcoming, and many don‚Äôt seem to care about their visitor.  A church can always improve it‚Äôs welcome experience to help newcomers learn about Jesus and find a place to serve.

Your church can too.

You and your church can learn new skills in personal evangelism, church hospitality, and missional engagement in the community.

I want to help you:

* Lead more church visitors to Christ as they get involved in your congregation.
* Remove the unnecessary barriers to a church visitor getting involved.
* Have awesome conversations about Jesus with people who need Him.
* Celebrate more baptisms of new believers this year.

Visit http://www.evangelismcoach.org/live-evangelism-training/travel-free-training/private-webinar/ and learn about doing a seminar for your team without the cot of travel.

name: EUROGIP
about:
EUROGIP is an observatory and a resource centre on the prevention and insurance of accidents at work and occupational diseases at international and especially European level. It is an organisation within the French Occupational Injuries insurance. 

ACTIVITIES :
- collaborating on projects of community interest,
- carrying out comparative surveys on occupational risks in Europe,
- collecting, analysing and disseminating information on occupational risks in Europe,
- networking by developing external relations and communication,
- coordinating a network of experts involved in the development of European and international occupational safety and health standards,
- coordinating the notified bodies for the regulatory certification of personal protective equipment and machinery at the French level (Ministry delegation).

name: Epic Change Windows
about:
Our Vision is Simple: To further enable innovation, leadership, and international competitiveness through capital availability

EPIC was formed as it became clear that there existed a bottleneck in the innovation infrastructures of Europe's leading innovation countries such as Sweden, Finland, and Denmark. Companies could originate and find seed capital, but that capital would be stranded as the companies and early investors looked for ways to grow beyond the first stages. Exits and further capital have become scarce for a variety of reasons. EPIC aims to bring awareness to these reasons and provide solutions in the short and long term.

EPIC shall do this by:
- Increasing and sponsoring academic research on the focused topic of 'Innovation Capital'
- Holding and participating in events that inspire innovation leaders, bring investors together with innovative opportunities, and help to
  promote international expansion and competitiveness of firms.
- Bringing light to the existing opportunities and limitations of our various regions' innovation systems with respect to their capital
  availability in later stages.

EPIC strives to empower people to utilize and strengthen their talents for leadership.  As a part of this, we are actively involved with developing and coaching innovation leaders (intrapreneurs and entrepreneurs) to enable them to attract capital.

name: Environmental Mechanics AB
about:
We develop, build and sell data loggers and probes for geotechnical investigations and drill data recordning in general.  All is done at our facilities in Sweden. 

Our data loggers are fully digital (CANopen) and covers all common types of measurement parameters (Force, Drill speed, Depth, RPM, Rotation pressure, etc etc). Our loggers are mounted on several types of drill rigs e.g. Sandvik DE140 Diamond core, Geomachine, Geotech , Geawelltech, HAFO etc. Data loggers for MWD and CPTu have been used together with several types of direct push- and drill rigs.

We offer CPTu for 1, 5, 10 or 20 tons. We have three types of CPTu:
   - Corded
   - Cordless with memory
   - Cordless with memory and acoustic real time data transfer
+ Seismic add on
+ Resistivity/Conductivity add-on

A new vane shear test system has recently passed beta testing and is now available for orders. The system measures torque both on the surface and with a probe in situ. Measuring torque on surface provides information for the operator to use when executing the test. Measuring in situ eliminates losses like rod friction and gives you accurate data. Curves for both surface- and in situ data are presented in the report generated by the system. A table with all data is also generated.

Lime column probe - For running lime column penetration tests. This probe is with built in memory and is available with acoustic transfer system for real time data presentation.

We also manufacture two types of CPT direct push rigs:
   - 20 ton push frame with optional  hydraulic support legs and trolley for manual relocation. This unit is also suitable for truck mounting. A hand held anchoring system with four augers is also included in the system.
   - Super compact CPT direct push crawler with 20 ton capacity. Fully equipped with outriggers and anchoring system. Suitable for transport on car trailer or a pickup truck
Both units are robust and manufactured with high quality components.

name: European Union Of Jewish Students
about:
The European Union of Jewish Students (EUJS) is a pluralistic, inclusive and non-partisan umbrella organisation. We support Jewish student unions throughout Europe and represent its members in international institutions and organisations.

Founded in 1978, EUJS is the umbrella for 36 national Jewish student unions.

Cognizant of the religious, linguistic and cultural diversity that make up the European Jewish community, EUJS strives to present a variety of perspectives through its leadership training programs, educational seminars and international conferences, all tailor-made to the needs of its students.  Throughout its history, EUJS has placed itself at the cutting edge of inter-cultural and inter-religious programming, as well as programming related to genocide education, advocacy and Jewish continuity in Europe.

EUJS is led by the president and eight board members who are elected by EUJS member organizations at the EUJS General Assembly. The EUJS headquarters are located in Brussels, Belgium.

De la infiintare si pana in prezent, compania si-a ajustat si completat in mod continuu portofoliul de produse, racordandu-se in timp real cerintelor pietelor: constructii, industrie, agricultura, cleaning.

Aria de acoperire s-a extins treptat in intreaga Moldova dar si punctual in tara, fiind stabilite parteneriate durabile in egala masura cu clientii finali, cat si cu reteaua de distribuitori ai companiei.

Seriozitatea si respectul fata de angajati, clienti si furnizori au facut posibila construirea unor relatii interumane si profesionale deosebite si consolidarea imaginii de partener de top construita in decursul anilor.

Politica coerenta de marketing relational coroborata cu managementul pro-client, au condus la parteneriate solide.
	
Compania continua politica de dezvoltare, in anul 2011 devenind unul din membrii fondatori ai Retelei Tehnik, grup cu acoperire nationala.

Astazi EUROTECH este un nume de referinta in piata de profil din Romania.

name: Ajax Business Associates
about:
Wie zijn wij
De betekenis en invloed van de voetbalsport op het maatschappelijk leven is groot. Het publiek en daardoor ook het bedrijfsleven tonen steeds meer interesse in het betaalde voetbal. In Nederland behoort AJAX gedurende een zeer lange reeks van jaren tot de meest toonaangevende clubs. Zij heeft een uitgebreide supportersaanhang van individuele personen, maar ook van bedrijven.

Vele van deze bedrijven zijn lid van AJAX BUSINESS ASSOCIATES (ABA).
ABA is de business club van Ajax.
De vereniging is in 1991 opgericht. De vereniging is ingeschreven in het verenigingsregister van de Kamer van Koophandel (V53735) en onderhoudt goede contacten met andere vergelijkbare organisaties.

Missie
De Ajax Business Associates | ABA, is een onafhankelijke vereniging met passie voor AFC Ajax. ABA is trots op zijn eigen identiteit en de geboden exclusiviteit in de mooiste zalen van de Johan Cruijff ArenA. ABA draagt niet alleen AFC Ajax een warm hart toe, maar beoogt ook de persoonlijke en zakelijke banden tussen de leden te bevorderen.

Visie
De doelstelling van ABA is om het grootste, meest exclusieve, onafhankelijke zakelijke platform in Nederland te zijn met voetbal als bindende factor.

Anyone can benefit from these teachings from beginners, to lay practitioners, and to true monastics regardless of where they live.

name: Fairer Finance
about:
Fairer Finance is a consumer group, research agency and consultancy founded in 2014. Our mission is to create a fairer financial services market - one that works for customers as well as the companies that serve them. 

Our customer experience ratings rank businesses based on customer polling, complaints data and our own unique transparency analysis.  

In 2017, we also launched product quality ratings, which rank financial services products based on their features. 

Our ratings are designed to help customers make better financial decisions, and also to encourage companies to compete on factors other than price.

Our consultancy business works with companies who want help improving their customer experience. We've reviewed and rewritten terms and conditions for several of Britain's largest banks and insurers, helping create documents which are clear for customers but also meet each firm's legal and regulatory requirements. We also review customer journeys - both on and offline - helping companies communicate in a consistent, clear and fair manner with all their customers.  

Some of the money we make is used to fund our policy and campaigning work, which we do on behalf of all UK consumers.

If you'd like to know more about what we do get in touch today.

name: OMG I WOULD LIKE
about:
OMG I WOULD LIKE is free-spirited, cheeky & adventurous in it‚Äôs collections.
 
What initially began as an individual journey to find that perfect piece that I would like for yet another of our own projects, quickly evolved into a shared experience.
It was to our surprise how many people stopped to ask for advice on how to get these items home & if we could help them & that's really how OMG has come to be, something for you & something for me. 
 
We fell in love with so many beautiful & unique pieces We couldn't just leave them behind. Confession, We have a total obsession with all things Natural, Black & White. 
 
Inviting that special piece into your home should not only be an expression of your own individual style, it should be beautifully crafted, functional or not, its unique & conversational all on its own. 
 
An appreciation of quality craftsmanship & a collaboration of my own ideas forms the  cornerstone of our brand. To enhance the concept of a piece gives me immense satisfaction & the peace of mind that we are introducing the best possible version of it into our collection.

name: Evolve Communities
about:
Home of the 7 Steps to Reconciliation & Allyship‚Ñ¢. Build a stronger, more inclusive business and Lead as a confident Ally

As Australia's trusted authority for Indigenous Cultural Awareness Training and Ally Accreditation, we deliver

‚ñ∫ Engaging, thought-provoking and shame-free education
‚ñ∫ Authentic cultural knowledge provided by an Aboriginal Elder and our team of Indigenous facilitators
‚ñ∫ Practical actions for Allies drawn from decades of lived-experience from our Community Engagement specialist
‚ñ∫ Something for every team size and budget from our accessible 45-minute online course, to deep-dive workshops and professional Accreditation Programs.

Nungamanladi! ‚Äì that‚Äôs ‚Äòhello‚Äô in Bardi language. We‚Äôre Evolve Communities.

Diversity, inclusion and a sense of belonging are crucial. Whether you need to attract and retain more Indigenous staff, or work more effectively with Indigenous stakeholders or suppliers, Cultural Awareness Training can bring a wealth of benefits.

Who are we?

Led by Bardi Elder Aunty Munya Andrews and Training and Facilitation expert Carla Rogers, Evolve Communities is a majority Indigenous-owned business and Australia's trusted provider of Cultural Awareness Training and Allyship Accreditation.

Indigenous Australians account for just 3% of Australia's population. For Reconciliation to happen, we all need to get involved.

That's why both Indigenous and non-Indigenous Australians design our programs and make up our team. Leading practical Reconciliation by example and demonstrating the values we hope to inspire is important to us. It‚Äôs one of the many ways we do things differently.

We've helped thousands of individuals and hundreds of organisations including: Cancer Council NSW, Edith Cowan University, BUPA, Woolworths and the Department of Prime Minister and Cabinet ‚Äì to name a few.

Our goal is to inspire ten million Allies to create a kinder, more inclusive Australia.

Get started with our 7 Steps to Reconciliation & Allyship‚Ñ¢

name: Estudiooca
about:
estudioOCA is an international studio founded in 2007, formed from its origin to focus on urbanism and landscape issues on a global scale. The studio‚Äôs primary offices are located in Bangkok, New York and Barcelona. 

estudioOCA takes a rational, pragmatic approach to urbanization and the landscape, responding to ecological, social, and political forces, and developing frameworks for transformation to meet current and future demands. The studio provides a conceptual rethinking of the public domain, revealing new opportunities for cities and open space. We work in parallel with, and in response to, infrastructure deployment, adapting mobility networks to greater bicycle and pedestrian uses, creating vital interconnections throughout urban environments. We work with cities to extract public space from outmoded uses. We work with architects, engineers, developers and other professionals to build socially interactive places. 

Our team‚Äôs multidisciplinary background, composed of landscape architects, architects, urbanists, landscape ecologists, social scientists, water resource engineers, and geoscientists, allows for a greater understanding of the interface between building, infrastructure, and landscape. Landscape serves as common ground where designed natural systems, urbanised space, and structures intersect.

The use of nature based solutions such as green infrastructure to help mitigate climate change, is one of the primary focus of estudioOCA work internationally. 

Please also visit our partner California registered non-profit organization (UCRISP) Urban Climate Resilient Infrastructure & Strategic Planning, here in Linkedin https://www.linkedin.com/company/76231444/admin/  as well UCRISP website ucrisp.org

name: St. Antoniusschool Amsterdam - Centrum
about:
De St. Antoniusschool is een eigentijdse basisschool in het hart van Amsterdam, dichtbij de Nieuwmarkt. Op onze school gaat leren hand in hand met een onderzoekende, nieuwsgierige houding en met ontwikkeling van zelfvertrouwen en verantwoordelijkheid.

Wij maken deel uit van de Amsterdamse Stichting voor Katholiek, Protestants Christelijk en Interconfessioneel Onderwijs (ASKO), de grootste organisatie voor primair katholiek/oecumenisch onderwijs in Amsterdam en omstreken. De ASKO staat voor excellent onderwijs en werkt vanuit verbinding, aandacht en ambitie.

Samenwerking met ouders vinden wij heel belangrijk. Wij hechten veel waarde aan hun actieve inbreng en een intensief contact met de ouders is voor ons vanzelfsprekend. Zo maken we samen van de school een plek waar leren een uitdaging is voor iedereen.
